{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_013YCxeyDtnkbgNuV3MWJtLK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me carefully validate the knowledge file against the source file by going through each check.\n\n**V1: Omission Check**\n\nLet me go through the source file section by section:\n\n1. **概要 (Overview)** - s1:\n   - Tool checks JSP files that compile successfully ✓\n   - JSP compilation happens during request unit tests ✓\n   - Note about taglibの閉じタグ example ✓\n   - All key points seem present\n\n2. **仕様 — 許可するタグの指定方法** - s2:\n   - Configuration file approach ✓\n   - HTML/XML output ✓\n   - List of specifiable syntax/tags ✓\n   - Check exclusions (permitted tag attributes) ✓\n   - EL expression examples ✓\n   - HTML comment exceptions (conditional comments, business screen tool comments) ✓\n   - Reference to 01_customJspAnalysis ✓\n\nI'm noticing the source mentions specific exceptions for HTML comments when they're disabled—conditional comments and business screen tool comments should not be flagged as errors, but the knowledge file seems to be missing the complete list of these exceptions.\n\nNow I'm moving through the specification for how to specify target files: arguments can designate files or directories, the tool recursively checks for .jsp files, extensions are configurable, and there are settings for handling mixed production and test files plus exclusion rules.\n\nFor the suppression method, I'm verifying that JSP comments placed above a line can exclude it from checks, with the requirement that tags must be on the same line and the comment must start with \"suppress jsp check\" — this applies even when JSP comments are otherwise disallowed. The specification includes a code example showing the import statements and tag library declarations.\n\nNow I'm checking the knowledge file to confirm the abbreviated example is acceptable — it shows just the suppress comment with the static